Representative_Docs: ['Like in any other job, teachers should be hired based on merit. Hiring based on seniority (first-come first serve basis) eliminates accountability and incentives to work hard. Merit based hiring puts students and hard working teachers first.', 'Teachers are now hired based on seniority, not merit. The best young teachers can be stuck in supply teaching roles for years, limiting diversity and equity in hiring. The teacher unions are determined to maintain this system. We think that is wrong. We are fighting to change it.', 'There is no Regulation 274 for surgeons, because we recognize there must be flexibility to hire based on merit, not seniority. Karen Spivak and the Toronto Star are correct: Regulation 274 does not serve our children well.']
